  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in Senate",
    "asOf": "2025-05-13",
    "date": "2025-08-12T16:25:19Z",
    "text": "Automotive Support Services to Improve Safe Transportation Act of 2025 or the ASSIST Act of 2025\n\nThis bill expands the definition of medical services for purposes of veterans\u00e2\u20ac\u2122 benefits to include additional medically necessary automobile\u00a0adaptations. Under the bill, the Department of Veterans Affairs may provide funding for the following medically necessary automobile adaptations for driver or passenger use:\u00a0ramp and kneeling systems, lowered floors, occupied and unoccupied mobility lifts, ingress or egress accessibility modifications, and adapted seating.\u00a0\n\nThe bill also extends the limitation on pension amounts for certain hospitalized or institutionalized veterans through September 30, 2032."
